sql:
SELECT 
    (SELECT SUM(quantity) FROM products) AS total_product_quantity,
    (SELECT SUM(loyalty_points) FROM customers) AS total_loyalty_points;

external_knowledge:
- Total sales refers to the sum of all sales amounts for products within a category; 
- Average customer loyalty points are calculated by taking the mean of loyalty points earned by customers who purchased products in each category; 
- Ranking by total sales from highest to lowest means arranging the categories in order of their total sales, with the category having the highest total sales appearing first.

sql:
SELECT product_id, description, price, quantity
FROM products
WHERE supplier_id = (SELECT supplier_id FROM suppliers WHERE supplier_name = 'SupplierA');

external_knowledge:
- 'big-spending customers' refers to those with a total order cost between $500 and $2000; 
- 'repeat customers' refers to those who have made more than one purchase; 
- 'shipped' is one of the possible statuses of an order (e.g., pending, shipped, delivered).
